article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- — Nana Antwi-Boasiako's 18 points helped SFA defeat New Mexico State 75-72 on Tuesday night. Antwi-Boasiako added 10 rebounds for the 'Jacks (6-5). Latrell Jossell scored 15 points, shooting 3 for 8 (2 for 6 from 3-point range) and 7 of 8 from the free-throw line. AJ Cajuste had 11 points and shot 3 for 10 (2 for 5 from 3-point range) and 3 of 6 from the foul line. The Aggies (5-8) were led by Christian Cook, who recorded 14 points. Brandon Suggs added 11 points for New Mexico State. In addition, Robert Carpenter had 11 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
